1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
So, with flowers or without flowers?

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Uh, with flowers.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Are you sure it's not better without flowers?

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,000
You look perfect either way.

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
I mean, you don't celebrate your 20th wedding anniversary every day, right?

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Marinette.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:15,500
Huh?

8
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,000
Could you come here please?

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,000
So?

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,000
What?

11
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
I trimmed my mustache.

12
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Is it too short?

13
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Should I shave it all off?

14
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
You look great, Dad.

15
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Except for one thing.

16
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Thank you.

17
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
No problem, Dad.

18
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,000
You're going to be late.

19
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Don't forget, Ms. Chamack is coming to pick up the Eiffel Tower cake in 30 minutes.

20
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,000
I'm counting on you.

21
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Yeah, yeah, don't worry, it's super easy.

22
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Mm-hmm.

23
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Wow, they've been married for twenty years.

24
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Isn't it beautiful, Tikki?

25
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Time flies when you're having fun.

26
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
And it stands still when you're doing homework.

27
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Hey.

28
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Marinette's family is one of the girls I hang out with.

29
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Yeah, I remember.

30
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
They make the best bread in all of Paris.

31
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Couldn't you have made a little effort to dress more appropriately?

32
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,500
What do you mean?

33
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:22,000
I took off my hat.

34
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
But this is a special day, you know.

35
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,000
What?

36
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,000
It's just a birthday.

37
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
No, this is a special birthday.

38
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
This family heirloom was made by one of our ancestors years and years ago.

39
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
It passes from one generation to the next on every 15th birthday.

40
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,000
And today, the day has come for it to be passed down to you, sweetheart.

41
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
That's really sweet, Dad, but I already have a watch.

42
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,000
It's synced to my smartphone.

43
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
But sometimes there's more than meets the eye.

44
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:52,000
I mean, our ancestors were a bit... ahead of their time.

45
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Of course, if you'd rather I got you a new pair of rollerblades instead, I'd understand.

46
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
No, Dad, I'd love to take it.

47
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,000
This is amazing, thank you.

48
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Are your friends waiting?

49
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Yeah, but I don't want to leave you.

50
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,000
It's fine.

51
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:16,000
No, no, you can go.

52
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Look, take good care of this, okay?

53
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,000
You can do this.

54
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Just remember the formula.

55
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Think, Marinette, think.

56
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Maybe I could think if you weren't distracting me with your encouraging words.

57
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Hello, Alya, what's up?

58
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
What?

59
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
What?

60
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,000
The bet between Alix and Kim?

61
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,000
No, of course I didn't forget.

62
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I even made the poster.

63
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
I know everyone's counting on me.

64
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Five minutes?

65
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,000
No problem, I'm already on my way.

66
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
I'll be right there.

67
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:54,000
But Marinette, we have to wait for Ms. Chamack to pick up her cake.

68
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
She'll be here in twenty minutes.

69
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
I told them I'd handle the poster and they're all counting on me.

70
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Plus, Adrien is going to be there.

71
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
You can never make it to Trocadéro in five minutes.

72
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
It's way too far.

73
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Not too far for Ladybug.

74
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Tikki, spots on!

75
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Looks great.

76
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Impressive, isn't it, Marinette?

77
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
You picked the wrong side to support.

78
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Looks like Alix is a no-show.

79
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Probably scared to race against an athlete like me.

80
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
You spoke too soon, Kim.

81
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Your ridiculous bet is about to end.

82
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
I'm gonna make you eat my dust, meathead.

83
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,000
You can't challenge me.

84
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
My neck is thicker than your legs.

85
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Is that a good thing?

86
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Let's review the rules.

87
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Two laps around the fountains.

88
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,000
About 500 meters.

89
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
The first one to cross the line will be declared the winner.

90
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,000
If Kim wins, Alix gives him her rollerblades.

91
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:10,000
If Alix wins, Kim can't make another bet until the end of the school year, unfortunately.

92
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,000
We're sick of these stupid bets.

93
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Enough already.

94
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,000
No more bets.

95
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
On your marks, get set... Hold on.

96
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Scared already?

97
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Can you hold this for me, Alya?

98
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
I don't want to think about it during the race.

99
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
No, girl, I can't.

100
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Guard it with your life, okay?

101
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:36,000
It's a family heirloom, but... Marinette, take this.

102
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
I need to record the race for my blog.

103
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,000
On your marks... get set...

104
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:50,500
Go!

105
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,000
Come on!

106
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,500
Go!

107
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,000
But she asked you to look after it.

108
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,000
I need to hold the watch.

109
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Huh?

110
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Need a hand?

111
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Yeah, thanks.

112
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:06,000
You should be careful, no matter how magnificent you are.

113
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
About holding things.

114
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,000
Final lap.

115
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Magnificent at holding things?

116
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Adrien.

117
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Let's see what you've got there.

118
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Is this some kind of old box or something?

119
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Careful, that's Alix's.

120
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
If it's Alix's, it's probably useless.

121
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Give it back to Adrien, Chloé.

122
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Fine.

123
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Yes.

124
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,000
I want a rematch.

125
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
That first pause threw me off.

126
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Did you do this?

127
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
I had to record the race.

128
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
So I gave it to Marinette.

129
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
She gave it to Adrien.

130
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,000
Chloé took it from him and dropped it.

131
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,000
Then you ran over it.

132
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,000
My dad gave this to me for my birthday.

133
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
This watch was a family heirloom.

134
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,000
It was an accident.

135
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,000
We didn't mean to damage it.

136
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Besides, I had nothing to do with it.

137
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,000
You're all guilty.

138
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Ah!

139
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Alix, wait!

140
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Way too much drama over one little push.

141
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,000
We still have time.

142
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,000
Hide, Tikki.

143
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Such disappointment, frustration, and negativity... how it thrills my heart.

144
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Fly away, my little akuma, and evilize her.

145
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Enjoy your meal.

146
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,000
This is Ms. Chamack.

147
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
Hello, yes?

148
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Yes, I know you want the cake immediately.

149
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,000
My daughter is home, she must be upstairs.

150
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
I'll call her right away.

151
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Maybe we can fix it.

152
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
This watch was amazing, unique.

153
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,000
It can't be fixed.

154
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,000
There has to be a way to restore it.

155
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,000
But how?

156
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Like going back in time and changing the future?

157
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Let me know when you figure out how to do that.

158
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,000
This can't be good.

159
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Hello, Dad.

160
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Hello.

161
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
I am Hawk Moth.

162
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:12,000
I'm giving you the power to take revenge on those who wronged you and to go back in time to fix the future.

163
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:16,000
But when the time comes, I will ask for a favor in return.

164
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Deal, Hawk Moth.

165
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,000
Oh, I have to go, Dad.

166
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
I can't keep Chamack waiting.

167
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,000
She's listening to music.

168
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Weird.

169
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,000
Run!

170
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Stop, Alix, what are you doing?

171
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
My name is Timebreaker now.

172
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:48,000
And I'm going back in time to save my watch.

173
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
And I'm going to use you to do it.

174
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Go back in time?

175
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,000
What did you do?

176
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,000
Why is he disappearing?

177
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,000
I needed his energy.

178
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Besides, that guy with all the bats was super annoying anyway.

179
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,000
He deserves to disappear forever.

180
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,000
And so do you.

181
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,000
We need to transform now.

182
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Tikki, spots on!

183
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Yes.

184
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Yes.

185
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Time out, Timebreaker.

186
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Please help me.

187
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,000
I'm so bad at this.

188
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Please, I'm begging you.

189
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,000
No.

190
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,000
Sweet thing.

191
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Always thinking of others before yourself.

192
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Wait a minute.

193
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Before everyone disappears forever... I have to get rid of that akuma.

194
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Where is that cat?

195
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,000
What?

196
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Time to transform.

197
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,000
Plagg, claws out!

198
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Come on.

199
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Come on.

200
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
A minute and a half.

201
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,000
You won't be able to stop me where I'm going, Ladybug.

202
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
Let me guess.

203
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
We're playing tag and you're it.

204
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Exactly.

205
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Don't let her touch you.

206
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
You missed by just a second.

207
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
No!

208
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
She sure doesn't waste any time, does she?

209
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,000
The more people she freezes, the further back in time she goes.

210
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:11,000
If we can't stop that akuma, the kids frozen in time will never come back.

211
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Get a grip on yourself.

212
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Now Timebreaker, seize her Miraculous, in her earrings.

213
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Cat Noir, no.

214
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Wow, six minutes with one touch.

215
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,000
He must have nine lives.

216
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,000
I have to go, the past awaits me.

217
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,000
Timebreaker, the Miraculous.

218
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Get Cat Noir's ring before he disappears.

219
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Just try it and see.

220
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Calm down, Hawk Moth.

221
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,000
I have a very good plan.

222
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Be patient.

223
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Come on, come on, come on!

224
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,000
Come on, come on, come on!

225
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,500
What happened?

226
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,000
What just happened?

227
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Wow.

228
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,000
We went back in time, didn't we?

229
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,000
What do you have there?

230
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Careful, that's Alix's.

231
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,000
What does it do?

232
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Is this some kind of old box or something?

233
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,000
If it's Alix's, it's probably useless.

234
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Give it back to Adrien, Chloé.

235
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,000
My watch.

236
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Chloé, put the watch down.

237
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,000
No!

238
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Ladybug, this time it's your fault.

239
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,000
I need more energy.

240
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:15,000
I have to go even further into the past.

241
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Ladybug, it's all Ladybug's fault.

242
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Could this be possible?

243
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Am I seeing double in my future?

244
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Or should I say double trouble?

245
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Fly away, my evil akuma.

246
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Savor this poor soul.

247
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:02,000
I can't explain now, but I'm you from a few minutes in the future.

248
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,500
She's right.

249
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,000
I can feel it.

250
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,000
She's you from the future.

251
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Crazy.

252
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,500
Listen.

253
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:11,000
I know this is unbelievable, but trust me.

254
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
I mean, trust yourself.

255
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
And Dad is going to call me.

256
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,000
I mean, he's going to call you in two minutes.

257
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:21,000
He's not happy because Ms. Chamack is waiting for you at the bakery door.

258
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,500
The cake.

259
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:22,000
The cake.

260
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,000
But I, I still... have time?

261
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,000
That's what I thought.

262
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Ms. Chamack came early.

263
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Now go and handle the cake situation.

264
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,000
Don't worry.

265
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Ladybug will handle this alone.

266
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,000
How do I get myself into these crazy situations?

267
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Let's go.

268
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Cat Noir, I don't have time to explain.

269
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
We have to capture Timebreaker's akuma.

270
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,000
My life depends on it.

271
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Which life?

272
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,000
I have nine.

273
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,000
I'm serious.

274
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,000
The akuma is in her rollerblades.

275
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
We have to release it.

276
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
Am I seeing double?

277
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Something else I don't have time to explain.

278
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:09,000
The energy from both of them is more than enough for both of us to go back in time.

279
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,000
I want my watch.

280
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Let's do this.

281
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Whatever you do, don't let either of them touch you.

282
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Take the Miraculous, Timebreaker.

283
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,000
If we work faster, these two can't stand against us.

284
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Then let's gather energy first, then we destroy them.

285
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Just a second, coming.

286
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:00,000
No problem, thanks.

287
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,000
Everything's fine.

288
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Sorry to keep you waiting.

289
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Mission accomplished.

290
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,000
I think you meant mission one.

291
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:13,000
And now there's mission two.

292
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Tikki, spots on.

293
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Yes.

294
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,000
We have enough speed now.

295
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,000
Let's show Ladybug and Cat Noir what we've got.

296
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Once we take their energy, we'll have time to go back and catch them.

297
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
And get our watch.

298
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
And you thought we were chasing them.

299
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Need a hand?

300
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,000
Thanks.

301
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,000
They're so fast on those skates.

302
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,000
And unstoppable when they're on the ground.

303
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
What if they weren't on the ground?

304
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Two Ladybugs.

305
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
I think I'm in heaven.

306
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Plan changed.

307
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
We'd better go back in time.

308
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Less of them there.

309
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:16,500
Works for me.

310
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,000
Let's not fail this time.

311
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,000
They're planning to go back in time.

312
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Lucky Charm.

313
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Got any ideas?

314
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Let me try to buy some time while you figure this out.

315
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

316
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Of course.

317
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:06,000
Let's freeze her while we pass by.

318
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,000
We're going too fast.

319
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:15,500
We can't stop.

320
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,000
Now.

321
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,000
Come on.

322
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
No more evil-doing, little akuma.

323
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,000
Time to de-evilize.

324
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,000
Gotcha.

325
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,000
Goodbye, little butterfly.

326
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,000
Miraculous Ladybug.

327
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,000
Pound it!

328
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,000
I believe this is yours.

329
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Awesome.

330
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
How did you fix it?

331
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,000
Thank you.

332
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,000
I shouldn't have given it to someone else to look after.

333
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,000
It was my responsibility.

334
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,000
My fault.

335
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Responsibility isn't something to take lightly.

336
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,000
I should have known.

337
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
You're absolutely right.

338
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,000
I'll be more careful next time.

339
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Thank you, Ladybug.

340
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Oh, man.

341
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
I was just getting used to there being two Ladybugs.

342
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,000
And now you'll have to get used to there being no Ladybug.

343
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,000
I have to go before I transform back.

344
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,000
One day she'll be mine.

345
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,000
It's only a matter of time.

346
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:51,000
You managed to escape me this time, Ladybug and Cat Noir.

347
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:56,000
But one day, whether in the past, present, or future, you will be destroyed.

348
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,000
And I will take your Miraculous.

349
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:02,000
I will be unstoppable.

350
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,000
So, did you have a nice anniversary?

351
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,000
Yes, of course.

352
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,000
But we had a close call this time.

353
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Yes.

354
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
I'm very sorry I kept Ms. Chamack waiting.

355
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Next time, wait for the customers in the bakery.

356
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
And not in your room listening to loud music.

357
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:25,500
Got it.

358
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,000
I promise I won't mess up again.

359
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Good.

360
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Because your mother is absolutely right.

361
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
And we trust her.